 EtherChannel Best Practices
!

! Use LACP (Active Mode Recommended)
interface range gi1/0/1-2
 channel-group 1 mode active

interface port-channel1
 description Uplink-to-Core
 switchport mode trunk
 switchport trunk allowed vlan 10,20,35,40,50
 spanning-tree guard root

! Best Practices:
! - Use LACP over PAgP
! - Ensure identical speed/duplex on member interfaces
! - Match trunk VLAN configuration on both sides
! - Avoid mixing L2 and L3 in same bundle
